                <p>
                  Drum rollers support the drum as it rotates, providing smooth and stable movement. Over time, these rollers can wear out, leading to squeaking, thumping, or grinding noises during operation. Worn-out drum rollers can also cause the drum to wobble or become misaligned, affecting drying performance. Replacing drum rollers involves disassembling the dryer to access and remove the old rollers, then installing new ones. Regularly checking and lubricating the drum rollers can help prevent premature wear and ensure quiet and efficient dryer operation.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="content__page-desc">
