                <p>
                  The blower wheel is responsible for circulating air through the dryer drum and venting system. It helps expel moisture-laden air from the drum, ensuring efficient drying. A damaged or obstructed blower wheel can reduce airflow, leading to longer drying times and potential overheating. Common issues include lint buildup, foreign objects obstructing the wheel, or the wheel becoming loose or damaged. Replacing the blower wheel involves accessing the dryer's internal components, removing the faulty wheel, and installing a new one. Regularly cleaning the lint trap and ensuring proper vent maintenance can help prevent blower wheel issues.
                </p>
