                <p>
                  Professional maintenance for your microwave involves a more
                  thorough inspection and servicing than what you might
                  typically do yourself. Here’s what you can expect from a
                  professional maintenance visit and how it helps prevent
                  repairs:
                </p>
                <ol>
                  <li>
                    <h3>Comprehensive Inspection:</h3>
                    <ul>
                      <li>
                        <b> Internal Components: </b>A professional technician
                        will open the microwave to inspect internal components
                        such as the magnetron, high-voltage diode, capacitor,
                        and control board. Identifying wear and tear early can
                        prevent more severe problems.
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <b>Electrical Connections: </b>The technician will check
                        all electrical connections to ensure they are secure and
                        not showing signs of damage or corrosion.
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <h3>Cleaning and Lubrication:</h3>
                    <ul>
                      <li>
                        <b>Internal Cleaning: </b>Professionals use specialized
                        tools to clean areas you can’t reach, ensuring that
                        dust, grease, and debris are removed from components
                        like the fan and motor.
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <b>Lubrication: </b>Moving parts, such as the door
                        hinges and turntable motor, may be lubricated to ensure
                        smooth operation and prevent premature wear.
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <h3>Diagnostic Testing:</h3>
                    <ul>
                      <li>
                        <b>Performance Tests: </b>The technician will perform
                        tests to ensure the microwave is heating correctly and
                        that all functions (such as the turntable and exhaust
                        fan) are working as they should.
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <b>Leakage Test: </b>A microwave leakage detector may be
                        used to ensure there are no radiation leaks, which is
                        crucial for safety.
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <h3>Calibration and Adjustments:</h3>
                    <ul>
                      <li>
                        <b>Power Calibration: </b>The microwave’s power output
                        can be calibrated to ensure it is operating at optimal
                        efficiency.
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <b>Door Alignment: </b>The technician will check the
                        door alignment and adjust it if necessary, ensuring a
                        proper seal and preventing energy loss.
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <h3>Filter Replacement:</h3>
                    <ul>
                      <li>
                        <b>Grease and Charcoal Filters: </b>If you have an
                        over-the-range microwave, the technician will inspect
                        and replace grease and charcoal filters as needed to
                        maintain effective ventilation and odor control.
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                  </li>

